    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Menu | Mechanism | Add 3D-Cam</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Add 3D-Cam</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-3D-Cam">3D-Cam dialog-box</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">What is a 3D-Cam?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">A <text styleclass="Element">3D-Cam</text> has complex surfaces with <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Flanks</text> that interact with Cam-Followers Rollers.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">Barrel, Cylindrical and Globoidal Cams</text> are <text styleclass="Element">3D-Cams</text>. <text styleclass="VariableName">Globoidal Cams</text> are also known as <text styleclass="VariableName-IT">Roller-Gear-Drives</text> and <text styleclass="VariableName-IT">Ferguson Cams</text>.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><anchor id="3DCAMPreparation"><keywords><keyword>3D-Cam<keyword>Preparation</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><text styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Prepare 3D-Cam</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="3" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Body Text" style="text-align:left;"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">You must prepare the model with five(5) elements.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text" style="text-align:left;"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">Also:</text></para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="VariableName">3 Mechanism-Editors</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> for a </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">Barrel Cam</text></li>
          </list>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="VariableName">4 Mechanism-Editors</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;"> for a </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT">Globoidal Cam</text><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Interface2" style="color:#ff0000;">All</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> are kinematically-defined <text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="color:#ff0000;">before</text> you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add 3D-Cam.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">We recommend you do these tutorials if you have not used this command before : <image src="Globe-www.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-size:7pt; vertical-align:sub;" figurelistinclude="0"></image><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="weblink" href="http://mechdesigner.support/index.htm?md-barrel-globoidal-cams.htm" target="_blank" styleclass="VariableName-IT">Tutorial 6C: Barrel and Globoidal Cams</link></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Top-Tip: Rename</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo"> the </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Mechanism-Editors</text> to the names of the elements you need to <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add 3D-Cam</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="SeeAlso">See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Rename-Element" styleclass="SeeAlso">Rename dialog-box</link></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:213px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:right;"><image src="GA-3DCam-Mechanism-Nametabs.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Prepare the view:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Table" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Click Visibility toolbar &gt; </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Visibility-Show-Model-in-Mechanism" styleclass="T_Menu">Show Solids in Mechanism-Editors</link></li>
                  <li styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Click Visibility toolbar &gt; </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Visibility-Show-Other-Mechanisms" styleclass="T_Menu">Show other Kinematic and Sketch elements</link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Body Text">To show the &apos;Other Kinematic and Sketch elements&apos; in each Mechanism-Editor:</text></para>
                <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Table" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="Body Text">Right-click each </text><text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism name-tab </text><text styleclass="Body Text">with an element you need to do </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add 3D-Cad</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Click &apos;Show with other Kinematic and Sketch elements&apos;</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="T_Menu">To hide Planes </text></para>
                <list id="3" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="T_Menu">View toolbar &gt; Spin</text> - you need to see all 5-elements before you can do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add 3D-Cam</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="T_Menu">Filters menu : Display Planes</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> &#160;- hide </text><text styleclass="Element">Planes</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> as they often hide the elements you need to do </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add 3D-Cam</text></li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
